Adelani Adepegba,Abuja The Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board has blacklisted 22 Computer-Based Test centres for allegedly defrauding 11, 823 candidates to the tune of N59m. Registrar of JAMB, Prof Is-haq Oloyede, said the CBT operators overcharged the candidates by more than N200 as service charge for the centres to effect correction on profile. They also allegedly bypassed the One-time password  required to initiate such changes. Oloyede disclosed this during  a meeting with operators of the delisted centres on Thursday in Abuja. The JAMB registrar added that the affected CBT centres owners would be prosecuted. Copyright PUNCH.
